    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>When my daughter (now almost 11) was about June&#8217;s age, one of our favorite things to make together was banana bread (or, more frequently, chocolate chip banana bread, because yum). Mashing the bananas was an excellent kid-friendly task, low risk, and while she was doing that I could start gathering and measuring other ingredients. Obviously she&#8217;s able to do quite a bit more now, and when we bake together these days we spend a lot of time talking about fractions!</p>
