    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>As a mother of 3 grown daughters, I love that you are cooking with June. Most of all I love that you don&#8217;t worry about the mess and just enjoy the moment. This time spent cooking and enjoying it, will repay you in spades. My oldest daughter lives across the country in Sydney now and we have great calls from the supermarket  or in her lunch hour talking about what she is cooking or how to make a childhood favourite. We all still laugh about the cooking adventures as  one daughter calls them. But the big winner from this era was &#8220;The Toddler Plate&#8221;&#8230;. or a tasting plate. Just raid the fridge, the pantry and the fruit bowl and choose what they wanted to eat . Cut up and arrange on plates, kept them busy for ages and they ate it all as they had chosen and made it. Great for fussy kids. We still whip up a toddlers plate after a busy day, albeit more olives and cheese and the addition of wine! The mention of June learning to crack eggs with your Mum was lovely to hear.</p>
