    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I feel exactly the same way about food and cooking with kids. My son (now 17) loved to cook as a kid. For his 4th birthday party, all he wanted were cooking ingredients, so that&#8217;s what kids brought &#8212; flour, grains, herbs, veggies fruit, nuts, olive oil, olives &amp; pickles (his favorites), etc.  Then the kids proceeded to cook, or at least treat it all like a cool science experiment. I cobbled together an outdoor kitchen in the yard.  (Clean-up accomplished with a hose. Even more fun!  These are 4-year olds, remember?)  Some of the &#8220;food&#8221; was edible, some not, but everyone tried at least a bite of each concoction. And they had a blast.  </p>
<p>To this day my son loves everything about food and eats well. He doesn&#8217;t have much time to cook, but food will always be a cherished part of his life.</p>
