    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>As a single parent, I find that cooking with my not-quite-2-year-old is easier than NOT cooking with him and having him vie for my attention. I never have time to do the measuring ahead, but he&#8217;s pretty patient about waiting his turn to dump things in the bowl (except eggs, which are too exciting to wait for). A friend recently shared a picture of her 6 year old making eggs-in-a-nest for he and his sisters; all mom had to do was turn on the stove. It really is amazing what these small people are capable of if we give them a chance! And seeing their growing confidence and knowing they&#8217;ll be able to feed themselves well makes up for any messes.</p>
