    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Helen</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2016/02/9390/#comment-45948"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-02-20T15:56:01-05:00">Saturday, February 20, 2016 at 3:56 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My mum used to make fruit cakes and my job was to mix the dried fruit into the dry ingredients. My fat little fingers would get lost in the bowl of flour separating the sultanas and raisins and things. Best kid entertainment ever! For my own kids I would figure out similar mixing opportunities like mixing the blueberries into the dry ingredients for blueberry muffins &#8211; it always gave me enough time to throw together the wet ingredients. But my biggest discovery was the egg slicer! I could get home from work, wipe off a few mushrooms and within seconds I had bought myself at least 10 minutes of bemused toddler entertainment while I whipped out most of dinner. That and the plastic knife and a few strawberries or bananas to slice up. Bliss ðŸ™‚   Oh, wait a minute&#8230;. what about those fun-filled times of both kids doing blind fold taste tests? Can you tell the difference between an orange or a yellow pepper? Pop on a blind fold and test your accuracy! There! Another 10 minutes of getting more dinner on the table ðŸ™‚</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
