<p>You&#8217;re right about how children can resist things their parents do well themselves and want them to like (for me, knitting caused a bit of friction). I remember my mom was adamant that we eat well-done beef, eschewing anything with even the slightest pinkness; and eat parsnips and radishes as often as possible. I DO eat thinly sliced radishes with butter and salt on good bread, but not the other two. I doubt that you&#8217;d ever make your child eat beef that tasted like a mouthful of cardboard!</p>
