    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#8217;m childless, but I do have a 2 1/2 year old niece who spends a good chunk of time with me. She loves helping in the kitchen, and the moment she sees me taking out the chopping board, she runs to get her small chair. She&#8217;s a fan of sprinkling herbs on anything (I&#8217;ve learnt to keep salt away from her!), stirring and mostly anything I let her do. One tip I think it&#8217;s necessary with such a small child is to use your biggest bowl if you don&#8217;t want everything to end up on the floor. I&#8217;ve also found that she&#8217;s more likely to try something new when she&#8217;s helped made it. And working on my patience is never a bad thing :).</p>
