    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Your beautiful attitude is the key to a good time.  Making dough ahead, brilliant!!!  And kids do want to contribute in meaningful ways.  And they can.  When I was nine, my mother and aunt decided I was to &#8220;keep house&#8221; for my 65 year old grandfather while my grandmother had knee surgery and rehab (8 weeks then, now would be 2 days at most).  I knew how to make Jello.  But I could read and follow instructions, and I had my mom and aunt for back up (my grandparents farm was in the middle).  It was an empowering, amazingly, life-changing experience.  Pushing a grocery cart ALONE, a signed blank check in my pocket, I was both thrilled and terrified.  My grandfather was a delight, so that helped!!</p>
