    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Great little list, and so true. Our kids love &#8220;mixing it up&#8221; in the kitchen and there&#8217;s always a make or bake day when they&#8217;re at home on a break from school. Hell, we even set-up a &#8220;Kids in the Kitchen&#8221; section on our cooking forums so parents and grandparents can share tips and recipes.</p>
<p>Patience is the key. They&#8217;re not Cordon Bleu trained chefs and they absolutely love making a mess, so you can&#8217;t be too strict or stuffy about it &#8211; just relax and roll with it. Besides, it&#8217;s always fun and there&#8217;s always that great moment at the end when we do the &#8220;taste test&#8221; &#8211; will it be &#8220;Hmmmm&#8221; or will it be &#8220;Urghhh&#8221; ?</p>
